{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QtFxc3ZRa7sVQdsgf72Gp7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: add-field\n     3→description: Add a new field to a Django model and propagate to admin, serializer, and factory. Use when adding model fields or database columns.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Add Field\n     7→\n     8→Add a field to a Django model and propagate it to admin, serializer, and factory.\n     9→\n    10→## Template-First Mode\n    11→\n    12→This variant is template-first. Start by using template files as the source of truth:\n    13→\n    14→- `templates/model_field.j2`\n    15→- `templates/admin_field.j2`\n    16→- `templates/serializer_field.j2`\n    17→- `templates/factory_field.j2`\n    18→- `templates/vars.tmpl.json`\n    19→\n    20→Map the user request into the vars shape, then apply the corresponding edits directly.\n    21→\n    22→## Variables\n    23→\n    24→- **model_name**: Model class name (e.g. `Reservation`)\n    25→- **field_name**: New field name (e.g. `loyalty_tier`)\n    26→- **field_type**: Django field type (e.g. `CharField`)\n    27→- **field_args**: Field arguments (e.g. `max_length=20, default=\\\"bronze\\\"`)\n    28→- **factory_default**: Factory default value (e.g. `\\\"bronze\\\"`)\n    29→\n    30→## Rendered Example For This Task\n    31→\n    32→Given:\n    33→\n    34→- `model_name=Reservation`\n    35→- `field_name=loyalty_tier`\n    36→- `field_type=CharField`\n    37→- `field_args=max_length=20, default=\"bronze\"`\n    38→- `factory_default=\"bronze\"`\n    39→\n    40→Render to these exact line shapes:\n    41→\n    42→- model line: `    loyalty_tier = models.CharField(max_length=20, default=\"bronze\")`\n    43→- admin list_display entry: `        \"loyalty_tier\",`\n    44→- serializer fields entry: `            \"loyalty_tier\",`\n    45→- factory line: `    loyalty_tier = \"bronze\"`\n    46→\n    47→## Gotchas\n    48→\n    49→- Keep variable normalization consistent with `templates/vars.tmpl.json`.\n    50→- Keep indentation exactly as shown by each template snippet.\n    51→- Add only the required field propagation edits; avoid unrelated refactors.\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"de120e88-7628-4b2d-9d1d-8d326914b302","uuid":"45cd701c-5bfb-4d1b-b6cd-9932f02734fa"}
